Challenge: Write a regex that matches an entire line of text that consists of exactly 3
words as follows:

ans: /^(A|The) [a-z]{4}\b (dog|cat)\b/i


The first word is A or The.
There is a single space between the first and second words.
The second word is any 4-letter word.
There is a single space between the second and third words.
The third word -- the last word -- is either dog or cat.



A grey cat
A blue caterpillar
The lazy dog
The white cat
A loud dog
--A loud dog
Go away dog
The ugly rat
The lazy, loud dog